{"title":"Found: A.S.Solutions Flat Mount Adapters for Post Mount and IS frames and forks","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/07/12/found-a-s-solutions-flat-mount-adapters-for-post-mount-and-is-frames-and-forks/","date":1626111200000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p>Back when disc brakes were in their infancy, I went on a mythical quest to track down an A2Z disc brake adapter to fit my odd-ball Manitou fork. Fast forward 20-some years, and not much has changed. There are probably fewer brake standards these days, but it still seems like you never have the right adapter for the brake you’re trying to mount.</p><p>The industry got pretty close to fully adopting the post mount standard, only for Flat Mount to slide in and take over the dropbar scene. Which may leave you with an older frame and fork that’s incompatible with newer disc brakes from SRAM, Shimano, and Campagnolo. Fortunately, A.S.Solutions is here to help.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123232/160pm-160fm-03-flat-mount-caliper-on-post-mount-570x570-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123232/160pm-160fm-03-flat-mount-caliper-on-post-mount-570x570-1.jpg\" alt=\"flat mount brake caliper adapter for post mount frame\" width=\"570\" height=\"570\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123232/160pm-160fm-03-flat-mount-caliper-on-post-mount-570x570-1.jpg 570w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123232/160pm-160fm-03-flat-mount-caliper-on-post-mount-570x570-1-297x297.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123232/160pm-160fm-03-flat-mount-caliper-on-post-mount-570x570-1-120x120.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123232/160pm-160fm-03-flat-mount-caliper-on-post-mount-570x570-1-420x420.jpg 420w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 570px) 100vw, 570px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb25 src ng ngcb25 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123232/160pm-160fm-03-flat-mount-caliper-on-post-mount-570x570-1.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123232/160pm-160fm-03-flat-mount-caliper-on-post-mount-570x570-1.jpg 570w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123232/160pm-160fm-03-flat-mount-caliper-on-post-mount-570x570-1-297x297.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123232/160pm-160fm-03-flat-mount-caliper-on-post-mount-570x570-1-120x120.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123232/160pm-160fm-03-flat-mount-caliper-on-post-mount-570x570-1-420x420.jpg 420w\"></a></p><p>A.S.Solutions? That apparently stands for Andre Sutton Solutions, and while the name seems to be a bit of a joke, the products are all serious solutions. Sutton writes that A.S.Solutions is “currently a one person operation with only the anodizing being done buy local company. I am doing this part time so quantities will be very limited.” That means the entire catalog is designed, machined, and finished in Edmonton, Canada.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123253/Shimano-GRX-Caliper-Post-Mount.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123253/Shimano-GRX-Caliper-Post-Mount.jpg\" alt=\"flat mount brake caliper adapter for post mount fork\" width=\"800\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123253/Shimano-GRX-Caliper-Post-Mount.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123253/Shimano-GRX-Caliper-Post-Mount-297x297.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123253/Shimano-GRX-Caliper-Post-Mount-120x120.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123253/Shimano-GRX-Caliper-Post-Mount-768x768.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123253/Shimano-GRX-Caliper-Post-Mount-696x696.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123253/Shimano-GRX-Caliper-Post-Mount-420x420.jpg 420w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb25 src ng ngcb25 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123253/Shimano-GRX-Caliper-Post-Mount.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123253/Shimano-GRX-Caliper-Post-Mount.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123253/Shimano-GRX-Caliper-Post-Mount-297x297.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123253/Shimano-GRX-Caliper-Post-Mount-120x120.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123253/Shimano-GRX-Caliper-Post-Mount-768x768.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123253/Shimano-GRX-Caliper-Post-Mount-696x696.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123253/Shimano-GRX-Caliper-Post-Mount-420x420.jpg 420w\"></a></p><p>We’ve seen adapters to go the other way, with the ability to run post mount brakes on flat mount frames and forks. But to our knowledge, this is one of the first adapters to allow flat mount calipers to be used on post mount or even IS (51mm International Standard) frames and forks.</p><h2>Post Mount to Flat Mount Brake Adapter</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123245/Flat-mount-caliper-adapter-for-post-mount-frame-160mm-rotor.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123245/Flat-mount-caliper-adapter-for-post-mount-frame-160mm-rotor.jpg\" alt=\"how to mount flat mount brake caliper on post mount frame\" width=\"759\" height=\"347\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123245/Flat-mount-caliper-adapter-for-post-mount-frame-160mm-rotor.jpg 759w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123245/Flat-mount-caliper-adapter-for-post-mount-frame-160mm-rotor-297x136.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123245/Flat-mount-caliper-adapter-for-post-mount-frame-160mm-rotor-120x55.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123245/Flat-mount-caliper-adapter-for-post-mount-frame-160mm-rotor-696x318.jpg 696w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 759px) 100vw, 759px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb25 src ng ngcb25 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123245/Flat-mount-caliper-adapter-for-post-mount-frame-160mm-rotor.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123245/Flat-mount-caliper-adapter-for-post-mount-frame-160mm-rotor.jpg 759w,https://bikerumor.com/ez