umor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123236/Flat-mount-caliper-adapter-for-post-mount-frame-140mm-frame-and-fork-mount-for-140mm-and-160mm-rotor-485x420.jpg 485w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123236/Flat-mount-caliper-adapter-for-post-mount-frame-140mm-frame-and-fork-mount-for-140mm-and-160mm-rotor-534x462.jpg 534w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb25 src ng ngcb25 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123236/Flat-mount-caliper-adapter-for-post-mount-frame-140mm-frame-and-fork-mount-for-140mm-and-160mm-rotor.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123236/Flat-mount-caliper-adapter-for-post-mount-frame-140mm-frame-and-fork-mount-for-140mm-and-160mm-rotor.jpg 760w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123236/Flat-mount-caliper-adapter-for-post-mount-frame-140mm-frame-and-fork-mount-for-140mm-and-160mm-rotor-297x257.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123236/Flat-mount-caliper-adapter-for-post-mount-frame-140mm-frame-and-fork-mount-for-140mm-and-160mm-rotor-120x104.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123236/Flat-mount-caliper-adapter-for-post-mount-frame-140mm-frame-and-fork-mount-for-140mm-and-160mm-rotor-696x603.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123236/Flat-mount-caliper-adapter-for-post-mount-frame-140mm-frame-and-fork-mount-for-140mm-and-160mm-rotor-485x420.jpg 485w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12123236/Flat-mount-caliper-adapter-for-post-mount-frame-140mm-frame-and-fork-mount-for-140mm-and-160mm-rotor-534x462.jpg 534w\"></a></p><p>A.S.Solutions offers three different adapters to run flat mount calipers on post mount frames or forks. These allow for a 160mm rotor on a 160mm mount frame/fork, and a 140mm or 160mm rotor on a 140mm post mount frame or fork.</p><p>There are three different adapters depending on the size rotor and mount you’re working with, and each has provided dimensions to be sure that it will work with your frame or fork. The provided <a href=\"https://www.assolutions.ca/flat-mount-caliper-to-post-mount-adapter-guide/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Flat Mount Adapter Guide</a> also provides a 1:1 print out, so you can make sure the adapters will work with your bike before ordering.</p><h2>IS Mount to Flat Mount Adapter</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12130601/is-fm-adapter-compatibility.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12130601/is-fm-adapter-compatibility.png\" alt=\"how to mount flat mount brake caliper on IS mount frame\" width=\"861\" height=\"300\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12130601/is-fm-adapter-compatibility.png 861w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12130601/is-fm-adapter-compatibility-297x103.png 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12130601/is-fm-adapter-compatibility-800x279.png 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12130601/is-fm-adapter-compatibility-120x42.png 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12130601/is-fm-adapter-compatibility-768x268.png 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12130601/is-fm-adapter-compatibility-696x243.png 696w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 861px) 100vw, 861px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb25 src ng ngcb25 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12130601/is-fm-adapter-compatibility.png\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12130601/is-fm-adapter-compatibility.png 861w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12130601/is-fm-adapter-compatibility-297x103.png 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12130601/is-fm-adapter-compatibility-800x279.png 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12130601/is-fm-adapter-compatibility-120x42.png 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12130601/is-fm-adapter-compatibility-768x268.png 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12130601/is-fm-adapter-compatibility-696x243.png 696w\"></a></p><p>Along with the Post Mount adapters, A.S.Solusions also offers an IS to Flat Mount adapter. The adapter allows for only 160mm rotors on the frame and 180mm rotors on the fork. Again, the adapter won’t work with all frames and forks, so make sure to follow the instructions to see if it will fit for you.</p><h2>More to Come?</h2><p>It’s not all just brake adapters from A.S.Solutions. The company currently offers an upgraded ‘Sherman Bolt’ for beefing up the suspension on your 2017/18 Rocky Mountain Element. There’s also unique Direct Mount derailleur hangers for Trek Stranglehold dropouts and Turners. In the future, the company is teasing a direct mount chainring and spider combination that will allow users to fine tune the chainline in 1mm increments.</p><p>Note that all prices are in Canadian Dollars, and shipping is available to the USA and internationally.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.assolutions.ca/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>assolutions.ca</em></a></p></div></div>","author":"Zach Overholt","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"69e7316c6bd6978ed7a11c33d299d4a1e01de75e948584cebd5af96a0deadcd7","category":"Cycling"}